The paper discusses the deployment of mMTC in 5G wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper proposes a solution to reduce RA collisions by clustering mMTC devices into groups, which involves the use of information theory and communication theory (cs.IT). The proposed solution also involves the use of device-to-device (D2D) links, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the reliability of D2D links, which involves the use of machine learning and signal processing techniques (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes an efficient grouped RA procedure, which involves the use of cryptography and security protocols (cs.CR).
